Version 2.0.0
- Kinento Order Reminders is now a community-supported open-source module
- The module is no longer maintained by Kinento
- The module is freely available under the MIT license

Version 1.3.4
- Updated the manual
- Various minor bug fixes

Version 1.3.3
- Added an option to consider last order update instead of order creation date as a criterium for sending reminders

Version 1.3.2
- Improved logging to a separate 'Kinento.log' file
- Added additional user feedback
- Fixes for missing sender name and email
- Various minor bug fixes

Version 1.3.1
- Added an option to enable/disable the module entirely for a store/view
- Improved multi-store/view support
- Added the "shippingdescription" variable for email templates
- Added "order_bis" as an alternative representation of the order in templates

Version 1.3.0
- Added a user guide (including installation, troubleshooting, FAQ)
- Embedded the folder structure for easier installation
- Added debug messages when sending emails

Version 1.2.6
- Added the possibility to exclude weekdays to determine an order's age
- Display an order's age in the overview grid
- Updated the order status list to match Magento 1.7's default statuses
- A message will now be added to orders which are canceled
- Fixed several minor bugs

Version 1.2.5
- Adjusted the module to enable translations
- Added default locale files (translations) for: English, German, Dutch

Version 1.2.4
- Fixed a bug where the cronjob would assume settings from the default store
- Major code clean-up
- Fixed several minor bugs

Version 1.2.3
- Added a feature to automatically cancel orders after a given number of days

Version 1.2.2
- Added a feature to distinguish payment types in the emails
- Set the cronjob to a higher frequency per default
- Updated the text displayed on buttons on the main grid
- Fixed a large number of minor bugs

Version 1.2.1
- Fixed a bug that occurred when installing Magento under 'admin/admin'
- Added the variable 'invoiceid' to the transactional emails
- Fixed a bug that obtained empty email addresses in Magento 1.4.1.0
- Added an option to send mass send out forced reminders

Version 1.2.0
- Added an option to send a reminder copy to a customisable email address.
- Added support for more than 2 reminders through an interval option.
- Added support for transactional emails. This makes it possible to edit the reminder templates from within the Magento system.
- Added an option to manipulate the reminder-send count from within the overview grid (reset, add, subtract).
- Added a button to manually send a reminder for one order, independent of filters or settings.
- Supports both Magento 1.3.x and 1.4.x through a setting
- Various minor tweaks

Version 1.1.2
- Fixed a bug that was introduced in version 1.1.1 using Magento 1.4.1 or higher, which would prevent email addresses to be read from the Magento database.

Version 1.1.1
- Added support for Magento 1.4.1.0, 1.4.1.1 and higher.

Version 1.1.0
- Added a settings panel entry to in- or exclude certain payment methods from the order reminders module. Orders with a payment method not chosen will not receive any emails.
- Added a column in the overview grid to display the payment type and whether it is disabled by the setting.

Version 1.0.2
- Fixed a bug where the filter in the grid would not perform filtering
- Added a confirmation message when sending reminders through the manual reminder button
- Added an option to perform a mass-action to enable/disable multiple orders

Version 1.0.1
- Added new options in the configuration panel to enable/disable attachments per customer type

Version 1.0.0
- Initial version
